$SIZES LIM1=892 $SIZES LIM2=892 $SIZES LIM6=892 $SIZES LTH=8
$PROBLEM MODEL_1
; Units: ; ====== ; Dose: mg ; Time: days ; Concentration: ug/ml ; Ouput: PD
$DATA ../../Data/dataNLME_popPD.csv IGNORE=@
$INPUT SKIP ID SKIP SKIP SKIP TIME2 TIME SKIP SKIP YTYPE SKIP DV SKIP CENS MDV EVID AMT CMT SKIP RATE SKIP SKIP AGE0 WT0 EFF0 SEX STUDYN TRT IND CL Vc Q1 Vp1 VMAX KM
$SUBROUTINE ADVAN13 TOL=6
$MODEL COMP = (Ac) ; Compartment 1 COMP = (Ap1) ; Compartment 2 COMP = (PD) ; Compartment 3
$PK ; Parameters Tinfinput1 = 1 ; Infusion rate (required)
; Auxiliary definitions for handling categorical covariates SEX_2 = 0 ; reference: 1 IF(SEX.EQ.2) SEX_2 = 1
; MU Referencing MU1WRAP_1 = THETA(5)*log(AGE0/66) + THETA(6)*log(WT0/72.6) + THETA(7)*SEX_2 ; BASELINE MU_1 = THETA(1) + MU1WRAP_1 MU_2 = THETA(2) ; kout MU_3 = THETA(3) ; EMAX MU_4 = THETA(4) ; EC50
; MU+ETA T_BASELINE = MU_1 + ETA(1) T_kout = MU_2 + ETA(2) T_EMAX = MU_3 + ETA(3) T_EC50 = MU_4 + ETA(4)
; Parameter transformations BASELINE = T_BASELINE kout = EXP(T_kout) EMAX = T_EMAX EC50 = EXP(T_EC50)
; Dosing compartments info F1 = 1 ; Ac
; Initial conditions A_0(1) = 0 A_0(2) = 0 A_0(3) = BASELINE
; Define TIMEOFFSET TIMEOFFSET = TIME-TIME2
$DES ; States DES_Ac = A(1) DES_Ap1 = A(2) DES_PD = A(3)
; Variables DES_kin = kout*BASELINE DES_Cc = DES_Ac/Vc DES_DRUG_EFFECT = EMAX*DES_Cc/(EC50+DES_Cc) DES_PD_rel = 100*(DES_PD-BASELINE)/BASELINE
; ODEs DADT(1) = -CL/Vc*DES_Ac-VMAX*DES_Cc/(KM+DES_Cc)-Q1/Vc*DES_Ac+Q1/Vp1*DES_Ap1 ; Ac DADT(2) = Q1/Vc*DES_Ac-Q1/Vp1*DES_Ap1 ; Ap1 DADT(3) = DES_kin*(1+DES_DRUG_EFFECT)-kout*DES_PD ; PD
$ERROR ; States Ac = A(1) Ap1 = A(2) PD = A(3)
; Variables kin = kout*BASELINE Cc = Ac/Vc DRUG_EFFECT = EMAX*Cc/(EC50+Cc) PD_rel = 100*(PD-BASELINE)/BASELINE
; just to avoid a NONMEM warning Y = 0.1
; Error model OUTPUT1 / PD IPRED = PD IRES = DV - IPRED W = THETA(8) IWRES = IRES/W IF(YTYPE.EQ.1) THEN Y = IPRED + W*ERR(1) ENDIF
; Assign variables to report in tables ETA_BASELINE = ETA(1) ETA_kout = ETA(2) ETA_EMAX = ETA(3) ETA_EC50 = ETA(4)
$THETA ; Model parameters 27.8 ; 1 (BASELINE) (27.8) -3.44 ; 2 log(kout) (0.032) 0.161 ; 3 (EMAX) (0.161) 3.02 ; 4 log(EC50) (20.5)
; Continuous covariate model parameters 0.1 ; 5 beta_BASELINE(AGE0) 0.1 ; 6 beta_BASELINE(WT0)
; Categorical covariate model parameters 0.1 ; 7 beta_BASELINE(SEX_2)
; Error model parameters 1.5 ; 8 Additive error OUTPUT1
$OMEGA 9 STANDARD ; 1 BASELINE 0.4 STANDARD ; 2 kout 0.04 STANDARD FIX ; 3 EMAX 0.85 STANDARD ; 4 EC50
$SIGMA 1 FIX
$ESTIMATION METHOD=ITS INTERACTION NOABORT NITER=10 SIGDIGITS=3 PRINT=1 $ESTIMATION METHOD=SAEM INTERACTION NOABORT NBURN=500 NITER=200 ISAMPLE=1 CONSTRAIN=1 CTYPE=0 SEED=123456 POSTHOC SIGDIGITS=3 PRINT=1 $ESTIMATION METHOD=IMP NOABORT EONLY=1 ISAMPLE=1000 NITER=10 MAPITER=0 SIGDIGITS=3 PRINT=1
$COVARIANCE UNCONDITIONAL MATRIX=S
$TABLE ID TIME TIME2 YTYPE MDV EVID DV IPRED IRES IWRES NPDE EPRED=XPRED ERES=XRES EWRES=XWRES NOPRINT ONEHEADER NOAPPEND FILE=project.pred FORMAT=s1PG15.6 ESAMPLE=1000 SEED=123456
$TABLE ID ETA_BASELINE ETA_kout ETA_EMAX ETA_EC50 AGE0 WT0 EFF0 SEX STUDYN TRT IND NOPRINT ONEHEADER FIRSTONLY NOAPPEND FILE=project.eta FORMAT=s1PG15.6
$TABLE ID BASELINE kout EMAX EC50 CL Vc Q1 Vp1 VMAX KM AGE0 WT0 EFF0 SEX STUDYN TRT IND NOPRINT ONEHEADER FIRSTONLY NOAPPEND FILE=project.indiv FORMAT=s1PG15.6
